Okay, okay...  I came back from Empire State Games yesterday, but I just didn't feel like blogging yesterday.  Anyway, I left on Wednesday for New Paltz; the bus ride was pretty good because there were about 15 people on it.  Finally arriving in New Paltz (at SUNY New Paltz, to be accurate), I checked in, went to my room and walked around the campus until 3 or so, when the Adirondack team had a meeting, and distributed the suits and all.  And it was cool because we all got Aquablades, so now I have an Aquablade for champs.  Best of all, it hasn't worn out yet, so it should make a difference with my times.

After the meeting, I went back to the room and waited for dinner, which began at 4.  At 4 I went down to dinner (it was actually in 3 big tents in a parking lot) and the line for the food strechted all the way through the parking lot.  So I decided to wait to eat, because I wasn't going to opening ceremonies that night, so I could eat whenever, whereas the people who went had to eat first.  As I was going back to the dorm, a huge storm popped up and people started running to get inside.  It was actually quite funny, seeing as how the tents started blowing over. :-P

Finally the storm died down, but since the tents were down, dinner was moved to the dining hall, so at around 6 I went there.  After dinner, I played some frisbee, went up to the room, played some XBOX, showered, read then went to bed, so I could wake up for the 6 am breakfast the next morning.

Next morning (Thursday) I woke up in time to get down to breakfast, eat, and get ready for prelims that morning, since I was swimming the 200 freestyle.  So I went to the pool, warmed up, and waited for my race.  I didn't do too bad in it: I went from a 2:28.81 to a 2:26.86 (:)).  I got 2nd to last, though, but hey; there's no way I could compete with a 2:07.

After prelims, we went back to SUNY and had lunch (we had to buy it ourselves due to budget cutbacks).  Food wasn't too bad, but it wasn't the best either.  I then slept until finals, and went to the pool to cheer for the team, even though I wasn't swimming.  Our team got a few golds, silvers and bronzes, but our relays sucked.  After finals, we came back, ate and played some frisbee (the team I was on lost, but my game was right on.)

Friday then was basically like Thursday, except that I swam the 100 backstroke instead of the 200 free.  In that, I went from a 1:19.83 to a 1:18.57.  Once again, I didn't make finals, but I came back for them to cheer on the team.  At the pool, we played some frisbee against some Hudson Valley kids during the 400 IMs (btw: they killed us.)  Then after finals, got some dinner back at the dorm, played some more frisbee (see a recurring activity here, yet? :-P ) and walked around campus, barely getting back into the dorm before the midnight curfew.

Saturday we went to the pool after breakfast, but I didn't swim in prelims.  However, I did make it to finals in the 4x100 Freestyle relay.  In that, I split a 1:06.47, so that made me happy.  After finals we had a pizza party, played some frisbee, and watched people jump into this really disgusting pond/lake on the campus covered in goose crap.  Ewww.  Once getting back to the dorms, I watched some Futurama, then went to bed.

Sunday I finally had to leave.  Nice car ride back home, and everyone here in Niskayuna is okay (like, no injuries), so everything's good.

BTW:  I got some mirrored goggles, which made me happy. :-P

Oh boy, I just got back from Starfish practice at Nisky High's Pool.  Our main set was more than 4700 meters!!!  If you have never had the joy of practicing in a 25 meter pool, don't.  Practicing in a 50 meter pool is fun, but not 25 meters.  It just becomes painful after a while.

Yeah.  So I guess there was supposed to be a sleep over tonight, but plans fell through :(.  Anyway, I'm very tired, and should go to bed now, but seeing as I don't have to be up until 7ish tomorrow, I think I'll stay up until the time I please. 

Or maybe not.  I'm very tired, and will be for the next week or so.

It's been a long time since I've updated. So this weekend I had a swim meet out in the metropolis of New Paltz, which if you don't know is an hour and a half away from the cultural center known as Niskayuna. I swam both days (Saturday and Sunday), but didn't stay over, so it was there and back, there and back again. Anyway, the Ulster County Pool Complex (in New Paltz) contains a 50 meter long course pool, which is, well, long. My times were all slower than my seed times, but they were the fastest I've gone since March. Also the Pool Complex is outdoors. It's really painful to do backstroke in an outdoor pool, because the sun gets in your eyes, and the water creates glare! PAINFUL! But as a bonus, this meet has prepared me a bit for Empires because Empires are being held at the Ulster Pool Complex, and I'm doing backstroke at Empires, so everything is good. Except my sleep pattern, since the past two days I've had to wake up at 4 a.m. to get there for warm ups. I'm bored, so I think I'll log off and maybe go do some biking.
